<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2006-03-16b.250.4" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/lord/100284" speakername="Baroness Hayman" colon="" colnum="250"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld199900/ldhansrd/pdvn/lds06/text/60316w01.htm#60316w01_wqn3">
	<p pid="b.250.4/1">asked Her Majesty's Government:</p>
	<p pid="b.250.4/2" qnum="HL4284">What steps they are taking to raise public awareness of bowel cancer and the national bowel cancer screening programme generally, and in particular in ethnic minority and hard-to-reach communities; and</p>
	<p pid="b.250.4/3" qnum="HL4285">What steps they are taking to maximise the efficiency of existing bowel cancer treatment capacity in advance of the roll-out of the national bowel cancer screening programme; and</p>
	<p pid="b.250.4/4" qnum="HL4286">When the Department of Health's central budgets for 2006&ndash;07 will be finalised and an announcement made on funding for the April 2006 roll-out of the national bowel cancer screening programme; and</p>
	<p pid="b.250.4/5" qnum="HL4287">What steps they are taking to ensure that testing kits will be made available for use by April 2006 for the roll-out of the national bowel cancer screening programme.</p>
</ques>
